{
  "article_id": "Gassaway1905_DCJ",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "Beginning due west of"
      },
      {
        "text": "Point Conception",
        "entity_key": "re_pc",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", on the"
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "coast, and continuing at irregular intervals as far south as the"
      },
      {
        "text": "Bay of Todos Santos",
        "entity_key": "re_todosbay",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in"
      },
      {
        "text": "Lower California",
        "entity_key": "re_baja",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", lie the"
      },
      {
        "text": "Channel islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "In this ideal region for the yachtsman, the fisherman and the hunter, one comes to feel like a new Crusoe on",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "his primitive isle",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_jf",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "And in very truth Crusoe's semi-mythical story was enacted upon",
        "tropes": [
          8,
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "one of these same islands",
        "tropes": [
          8,
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "though minus the man Friday and the happy ending.",
        "tropes": [
          8,
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The castaway",
        "tropes": [
          8,
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "in this case was a woman, a Danish emigrant left ashore through some mischance by the crew of a vessel that had sought shelter behind",
        "tropes": [
          8,
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "tropes": [
          8,
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "during a storm in the early [18]'50s.",
        "tropes": [
          8,
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "For over 17 years"
      },
      {
        "text": "the lone creature",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had lived unsought and forgotten, though the time at length came when, on the days the mist-clearing north wind blew, she would climb to the island's highest point and view the ranchers' herds grazing upon"
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "And at last, when hope and reason had both long died,",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the poor, wild, gibbering creature",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was found in her wolf's burrow among the hills by",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the advance guard of the otter hunters' fraternity",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who had long wondered at the mysterious footprints they marked upon the lonely sands.",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
}